title: High Oil Prices Lift Saudi Arabia, Bolster Prince's Economic Plans
description: A bonanza of extra revenue shows how high oil prices are benefiting the Persian Gulf’s resource-rich economies.

title: Peru President Pedro Castillo Plans to Dissolve Congress Before Impeachment Vote
description: Mr. Castillo, who was elected last year, said he would install an ‘exceptional emergency government’

title: Sister of Iran's Supreme Leader Calls for Overthrow of His 'Despotic Caliphate'
description: Badri Hosseini Khamenei also called on security forces to lay down arms and join the protesters demanding an ouster of the country’s Islamic leadership.

title: China's Xi Jinping Visits Saudi Arabia Amid Strained U.S. Ties
description: The visit could deepen the relationship between the world’s top oil importer and top oil exporter amid strained U.S.-Saudi ties and a global reshuffling of power accelerated by the Ukraine war.

title: Pope Francis Compares War in Ukraine to the Holocaust
description: The pope likened the war in Ukraine to the Nazi genocide of the Jews, in his latest escalation of rhetoric on the war.

title: Chinese Exports Fall at Steep Pace
description: In an indication of how the country’s pandemic restrictions and waning global demand is hitting China’s economy, exports fell in November at the sharpest pace in over two years.

title: Russia Moves to Bolster Defenses After Airfield Strikes
description: Russia took steps to strengthen its defenses following a string of strikes deep within its border, while Moscow’s forces launched drones and missiles at southern Ukraine.

title: Russian Oil-Price Cap Adds to Fiscal Pressure on Moscow
description: Fresh Western curbs on Russian crude sales might not affect Moscow’s public coffers immediately, but they add financial pressure that threatens the country’s sanctions-stricken oil industry.

title: Germany Arrests Suspects in Plot to Topple Government
description: More than 3,000 police officers including special forces conducted raids at 130 properties across Germany, Italy and Austria, in one of the largest operations of its kind in recent history, officials said.

title: EU Files Complaint in WTO Over China's Trade Retaliation on Lithuania
description: The complaint relates to punitive trade restrictions that Beijing imposed on the European Union country last year after its moves to support Taiwan.

title: China Scraps Most Testing, Quarantine Requirements in Covid Policy Pivot
description: China took another step away from its stringent Covid-19 controls, easing quarantine and testing requirements and curtailing the power of local officials to shut down entire city blocks and raise barriers to domestic travel.

title: U.S. Plans Broad Increase of Military Presence in Australia
description: The U.S. and Australia agreed to deepen defense cooperation amid growing concerns about China’s actions in the Indo-Pacific region.

title: Mexico's Congress Defeats President's Bill to Overhaul Election Agency
description: Mexican President Andrés Manuel López Obrador suffered a significant setback as opposition parties united against a proposal they said undermined the autonomy of the National Electoral Institute.
